nodes.bodyText:
Given what you said about the API this should actually be
update(data: StatusUpdate | FieldUpdate, locationId: string): Observable<Location>
where
interface StatusUpdateRequest {
    status: string
}
interface FieldUpdateRequest {
    ... // fields we can update
}
unfortunately we don't have much ability to change the API, so we just have to do our best to write types that model what the API wants. I'll try to pay attention to the design docs when making future suggestions.
The type of EntityService is going to conflict with this. Since we don't have a conventional REST API I don't think EntityService is really going to be able to help here. I would just use the http service directly.

